.TH "kcp" 1 "August 5, 2020" "dev" ""
.SH NAME
kcp \- Tool in command-line for KaOS Community Packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
kcp  [\-h|\-\-help] [\-v|\-\-version] [\-l|\-\-list] [\-u|\-\-update-database] [\-s|\-\-search [<app>]] [\-g|\-\-get [<app>]] [\-i|\-\-install [<app>]] [\-x|\-\-sort] [\-f|\-\-force-update] [\-N|\-\-only-name] [\-S|\-\-only-starred] [\-I|\-\-only-installed] [\-O|\-\-only-outdated] [\-d|\-\-asdeps] [\-V|\-\-information [<app>]] [\-\-debug]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Provides a tool to make the use of KaOS Community Packages.
.PP
With this tool, you can search, get and install a package from KaOS Community Packages.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-h|\-\-help
	Print this help
.TP
\-v|\-\-version
	Print version
.TP
\-l|\-\-list
	Display all packages of KCP
.TP
\-u|\-\-update-database
	Refresh the local database
.TP
\-s|\-\-search [<app>]
	Search packages in KCP and display them
.TP
\-g|\-\-get [<app>]
	Download needed files to build a package
.TP
\-i|\-\-install [<app>]
	Install a package from KCP
.TP
\-x|\-\-sort
	On display action, sort packages by stars descending
.TP
\-f|\-\-force-update
	On display action, force refreshing local database
.TP
\-N|\-\-only-name
	On display action, display only the name of the package
.TP
\-S|\-\-only-starred
	On display action, display only packages with at least one star
.TP
\-I|\-\-only-installed
	On display action, display only installed packages
.TP
\-O|\-\-only-outdated
	On display action, display only outdated packages
.TP
\-d|\-\-asdeps
	On install action, install as a dependence
.TP
\-V|\-\-information [<app>]
	Display informations about a package
